  - Sacrifice-Death=Renunciation-Detachment=The Rupture With Habit
By: Al-'Arabi al-Hasanî ad-Darqâwî
---
The systematic pursuit of meritorious acts and the multiplication of
supererogatory practices are habits like others; they scatter the heart. Let
the disciple therefore keep to a single invocation (dhikr), to a single
action, each according to what corresponds to him.
